name: Hypertension
title: Hypertension
description: SNOMED CT intensional (rule-based) value set for defining hypertension, available for a range of potential uses including problem-oriented views of relevant clinical information, clinical decision support rules, electronic patient registries, and data analytics.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Broad group of diagnosis concepts for hypertension (high blood pressure).),(Data Element Scope: Employs SNOMED CT concept hierarchies primarily in the Disorder (Clinical finding) branch, though some can be in the Situation with Explicit Context branch or the Procedure branch.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes systemic arterial hypertension: primary hypertension, secondary hypertension, complications of hypertension, and history of hypertension.),(Exclusion Criteria: Does not include pulmonary arterial hypertension, venous hypertension, or family history of hypertension.)
